###Is $\overline{AB}$ parallel to $\overline{CD}$?

Two lines are parallel if they have equal slopes.

Let's find the slope between $\maroonD{A(0,6)}$ and $\blueE{B(3,5)}$.

$\begin{align}
\dfrac{\Delta y}{\Delta x} &= \dfrac{\maroonD{6}-\blueE{5}}{\maroonD{0}-\blueE{3}}\\\\
&=-\dfrac{1}{3}
\end{align}$

Next, let's find the slope between $\purpleD{C(0,-4)}$ and $\goldE{D(-3,-3)}$.

$\begin{align}
\dfrac{\Delta y}{\Delta x} &= \dfrac{\goldE{-3}-(\purpleD{-4})}{\goldE{-3}-\purpleD{0}}\\\\
&=-\dfrac{1}{3}
\end{align}$

The slopes of $\overline{AB}$ and $\overline{CD}$ both equal $-\dfrac{1}{3}$, so the sides are parallel.
